{
  "local_port": 35472,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I get printouts of past IRCTC journey tickets?",
  "response": "If you need printouts of past IRCTC (Indian Railway Catering and Tourism Corporation) journey tickets, you can retrieve them using the following methods:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Retrieve from IRCTC Website/App**\n   - **Log in to your IRCTC account**: Visit [IRCTC's official website](https://www.irctc.co.in) or open the IRCTC Rail Connect app.\n   - **Go to \"Booked Ticket History\"**: Navigate to the \"My Transactions\" or \"Booked Ticket History\" section.\n   - **Select the ticket**: Locate the journey you want and click on it to view the ticket details.\n   - **Download and print**: Use the \"Print\" or \"Download\" option to save the ticket as a PDF and print it.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Use the PNR Number**\n   - If you have the PNR (Passenger Name Record) number of the journey:\n     - Go to the \"PNR Status\" section on the IRCTC website or app.\n     - Enter the PNR number and search.\n     - Once the ticket details appear, print or download the ticket.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Check Email or SMS**\n   - Search your email or SMS inbox for the ticket confirmation sent by IRCTC at the time of booking.\n   - Open the email or SMS and use the attached ticket link or PDF to print it.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Visit the Railway Station**\n   - If you are unable to retrieve the ticket online, visit the nearest railway station.\n   - Provide the PNR number or ticket details to the ticket counter or inquiry desk.\n   - They may be able to assist you in retrieving and printing the ticket.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Contact IRCTC Customer Care**\n   - Call IRCTC customer care at **139** or **011-39340000**.\n   - Provide your PNR number or booking details and request assistance in retrieving and printing the ticket.\n\n---\n\n### **Note**:\n   - Tickets are usually available for retrieval for up to **60 days** from the date of travel.\n   - Ensure you have the PNR number or booking details ready for easier retrieval.\n\nLet me know if you need further assistance!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
